Galeotti] Galeozzo Marzio (e. 1427- 1497), of Narni in Umbria, was a pupil of Guarino at Feri-ara ¹447-50· 'riu 1460 he taught classics and medicine at Padua; and then made use of his acquaintance with Janus Pannonius, a fellow-pupil under Guarino and now Bp. of Fiinfkirchen‚ to seek his fortune in Hungary.
